                    name="Video"
                    overlayButtonFontIcon="play"
                    overlayButtonIconKind="icon-font"
                    overlayButtonLabel="Watch 4:24"
                    overlayDescription="-"
                    overlayHeading="Discovery Files: Hepatitis C Virus"
                    placeholderImage="https://delivery-p157365-e1665873.adobeaemcloud.com/adobe/assets/urn:aaid:aem:291c562f-6fee-425f-9207-2023c490e566/as/discoveryfiles-hepatitis-c-virus-yt.png"
                    placeholderImageMimeType="image/unknown"
                    posterAccessibilityLabel="Discovery Files Hepatitis C Virus"
                    projectNumber="-"
                    uri="https://www.youtube.com/embed/rMy4Bo6Go7U?enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abbvie.com&amp;widgetid=2&amp;forigin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abbvie.com%2Fwho-we-are%2Four-stories%2Fwhat-does-it-take-to-discover-a-new-medicine.html&amp;aoriginsup=1&amp;vf=1"
                    videoContentLayout="none"/>
                <block_9
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Building off their own research around HIV, the team aimed to find a way to stop the virus from replicating, lowering the viral load in the body and blocking proteins necessary for the virus’ survival. But the journey didn’t end there – it took years and many iterations until the real “aha” moment; the team had to work counter-intuitively, building molecules larger instead of smaller and targeting all major HCV genotypes instead of just some.&lt;/p>&lt;p>The stories of the Discovery Files series demonstrate that “good enough” is never good enough, for those at AbbVie searching for tomorrow’s scientific breakthroughs. One of the series’ featured scientists, Seble Wagaw, VP, development sciences, AbbVie, explains it best. “The journey show(s) us that we have the capability and the drive to keep working every day to discover and develop new treatments for people who need them.”&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_9>
